Internal obstruction of water toxin can make the disease condition critical.
Internal stirring of liver wind can cause convulsions.
Phlegm-heat clouding the heart orifices can cause coma.
Disharmony of the Thoroughfare and Conception vessels can cause gynecological syndromes.
Disharmony between nutritive Qi and defensive Qi can cause aversion to wind and spontaneous sweating.
Failure of stomach-Qi to descend can cause vomiting and hiccup.
Failure of lung-Qi to disperse can cause nasal obstruction and cough.
Spleen deficiency producing dampness can form phlegm-fluid retention.
